🤖 Why Amazon Bedrock?

We chose Amazon Bedrock for building this AI agent because:

It is a fully managed service, eliminating infrastructure overhead

Provides secure access to foundation models within AWS ecosystem

Seamlessly integrates with AWS services like Lambda, API Gateway, etc.

Ideal for building scalable and production-ready AI agents



🧠 Model Selection: Nova Pro

We selected Nova Pro because:

It is a high-capability general-purpose model

Offers strong price-to-performance ratio

Optimized for agent-based workflows and reasoning tasks

Capable of making intelligent decisions and tool calls




⚙️ Agent Creation Steps
🪜 Step 1: Open Bedrock Console

Navigate to:
Amazon Bedrock → Agents → Create Agent



🪜 Step 2: Configure Agent Details

Fill in the required details:

Agent Name:
Ritik-AWS-Admin-Agent

Description:
AWS Admin assistant for discovering cost optimization opportunities and managing cloud resources intelligently



🪜 Step 3: Assign IAM Role

Select: Create and use a new service role

This allows the agent to securely interact with AWS services



🪜 Step 4: Select Model

Choose model: Nova Pro

👉 This model will act as the brain of the agent, responsible for:

Understanding user queries

Making decisions

Triggering appropriate AWS actions



🪜 Step 5: Save and Exit

Click Save and Exit

Your agent is now successfully created 🎉




🧠 What Happens Internally?

Once the agent is created:

Nova Pro processes user input

Interprets intent using natural language understanding

Decides whether to:

Respond directly OR

Call AWS tools (via Lambda functions)

Enables intelligent automation with human-in-the-loop control

